on":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to travel"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"writer","examples":[{"text":"بِأَيْدِي سَفَرَةٍ كِرَامٍ بَرَرَةٍ","english":"In the hands of scribes, noble and dutiful."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare سَفَر (safar, “journey, travel”).\nCognate with Akkadian 𒊭𒉺𒀸 (šapārum, “to send to”) and Hebrew ספר (“s-p-r”) 4th ethnology.\n\nTerminology of the religious sphere borrowed from Aramaic סִפְרָא (sip̱rā, “writing, book”) / ܣܷܦܪܴܐ (sep̱rā, “writing, book”); and compare Hebrew סֵפֶר (sḗp̄er, “writing, book”) and סוֹפֵר (sōp̄ḗr, “writer”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19945","headword_ar":"سَافِرٌ","root":"sfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[act. part. n. of 1:] A woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having her face uncovered:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Mgh, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaAfiru","text_ar":"سَوَافِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  And a horse (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having little flesh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAfiru All~aHomi","text_ar":"سَافِرُ اللَّحْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a phrase used by Ibn-Mukbil. (TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safiyrN","text_ar":"سَفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musaAfirN","text_ar":"مُسَافِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A writer; a scribe:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Akh, S, M, K:) in the Nabathæan language"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAfiraA","text_ar":"سَافِرَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarapN","text_ar":"سَفَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Akh, S, M, K:) which is also applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"angels who register actions."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Mgh","K","Akh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}